One more thing - for the home page, it currently uses `getServerSideProps` which gives it `req.headers['user-agent']`. In App Router:
- We can use `headers()` from `next/headers` in a Server Component
- We don't call `getServerSideProps` anymore; we just make the component `async`
- Since we access `headers()`, the page is automatically dynamically rendered

For the home page's navigation button using `router.push`:
- In App Router, client components use `useRouter` from `next/navigation`
- The home page component is a server component (it fetches data and uses `headers()`)
- If it needs `useRouter`, it needs to be a client component OR we extract the interactive part
- Actually, looking at the original code more carefully, the button calls `router.push('/blog')` which is client-side navigation
